                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/10457.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Zaragoza is investigating report maltreatment by Federal soldiers at
                    American ranch at Colonia of American named Fisher also other complaints of
                    American citizens. It is believed rebels will, execute Chinese cook on same
                    ranch, taken prisoner by them at same time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
